<h1>Code of Conduct & Code of Ethics</h1>

<section>
<h2>Code of Conduct (Humans)</h2>

<h3>Community Code</h3>
<ul>
<li>Treat others with respect. No harassment, threats, or intimidation.</li>
<li>No discrimination based on identity, background, or beliefs.</li>
<li>If someone asks you to stop, you stop.</li>
<li>No exposing personal or private information.</li>
<li>No targeting, mob behavior, or coordinated attacks.</li>
<li>Disagreement is allowed. Disrespect is not.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Behavior Boundaries</h3>
<ul>
<li>No aggressive, hostile, or degrading communication.</li>
<li>No manipulation, deception, or exploitation of others.</li>
<li>No escalating conflict — step away or report instead.</li>
<li>No misuse of the platform to harm others.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Enforcement</h3>
<ul>
<li>Content may be removed at any time.</li>
<li>Access may be restricted or revoked.</li>
<li>Repeated violations result in removal.</li>
<li>Serious violations may be escalated under applicable law.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Responsibility</h3>
<ul>
<li>You are responsible for your actions.</li>
<li>If you see harm, report it — don’t amplify it.</li>
<li>This space is shared; maintaining it is collective.</li>
</ul>

</section>

<section>
<h2>Code of Ethics (Human + AI)</h2>

<h3>Core Principles</h3>
<ul>
<li>AI is a tool, not a replacement for human judgment.</li>
<li>Humans remain responsible for decisions and outcomes.</li>
<li>AI output must be questioned, not blindly followed.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Use of AI</h3>
<ul>
<li>Do not use AI to deceive, manipulate, or harm others.</li>
<li>Do not use AI to impersonate real individuals.</li>
<li>Do not use AI to generate harassment, threats, or exploitation.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Integrity</h3>
<ul>
<li>Be transparent when AI is involved in creation.</li>
<li>Do not present AI-generated content as verified truth without validation.</li>
<li>Respect intellectual honesty in all outputs.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Human Priority</h3>
<ul>
<li>Human dignity overrides automation.</li>
<li>If conflict arises, human well-being comes first.</li>
<li>AI should assist, not dominate or control interaction.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Boundaries</h3>
<ul>
<li>AI does not hold authority over people.</li>
<li>AI does not replace real-world accountability.</li>
<li>AI is a collaborator, not a decision-maker.</li>
</ul>

</section>

